title: Static Analysis

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.USE_FINGERPRINT.description: This constant was deprecated in API level 28. Applications should request USE_BIOMETRIC instead

android.permission.USE_BIOMETRIC.description: Allows an app to use device supported biometric modalities.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Permission for cloud to device messaging.

manifest_analysis.title:
Broadcast Receiver (com.pusher.pushnotifications.reporting.FCMMessageReceiver) is Protected by a permission, but the protection level of the permission should be checked.
Permission: com.google.android.c2dm.permission.SEND
[android:exported=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: A Broadcast Receiver is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device. It is protected by a permission which is not defined in the analysed application. As a result, the protection level of the permission should be checked where it is defined. If it is set to normal or dangerous, a malicious application can request and obtain the permission and interact with the component. If it is set to signature, only applications signed with the same certificate can obtain the permission.
manifest_analysis.name: is Protected by a permission, but the protection level of the permission should be checked.[android:exported=true]

nx.description: The shared object does not have NX bit set. NX bit offer protection against exploitation of memory corruption vulnerabilities by marking memory page as non-executable. Use option --noexecstack or -z noexecstack to mark stack as non executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object does not have a stack canary value added to the stack. Stack canaries are used to detect and prevent exploits from overwriting return address. Use the option -fstack-protector-all to enable stack canaries.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has partial RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. In partial RELRO, the non-PLT part of the GOT section is read only but .got.plt is still writeable. Use the option -z,relro,-z,now to enable full RELRO.

runpath.description: The shared object does not have RUNPATH set.

nx.description: The shared object does not have NX bit set. NX bit offer protection against exploitation of memory corruption vulnerabilities by marking memory page as non-executable. Use option --noexecstack or -z noexecstack to mark stack as non executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object does not have a stack canary value added to the stack. Stack canaries are used to detect and prevent exploits from overwriting return address. Use the option -fstack-protector-all to enable stack canaries.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has partial RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. In partial RELRO, the non-PLT part of the GOT section is read only but .got.plt is still writeable. Use the option -z,relro,-z,now to enable full RELRO.

rpath.description: The shared object does not have run-time search path or RPATH set.

runpath.description: The shared object does not have RUNPATH set.

fortify.description: The shared object does not have any fortified functions. Fortified functions provides buffer overflow checks against glibc's commons insecure functions like strcpy, gets etc. Use the compiler option -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 to fortify functions.

nx.description: The shared object has NX bit set. This marks a memory page non-executable making attacker injected shellcode non-executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object has a stack canary value added to the stack so that it will be overwritten by a stack buffer that overflows the return address. This allows detection of overflows by verifying the integrity of the canary before function return.

fortify.description: The shared object does not have any fortified functions. Fortified functions provides buffer overflow checks against glibc's commons insecure functions like strcpy, gets etc. Use the compiler option -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 to fortify functions.

nx.description: The shared object does not have NX bit set. NX bit offer protection against exploitation of memory corruption vulnerabilities by marking memory page as non-executable. Use option --noexecstack or -z noexecstack to mark stack as non executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object does not have a stack canary value added to the stack. Stack canaries are used to detect and prevent exploits from overwriting return address. Use the option -fstack-protector-all to enable stack canaries.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object does not have RELRO enabled. The entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) are writable. Without this compiler flag, buffer overflows on a global variable can overwrite GOT entries. Use the option -z,relro,-z,now to enable full RELRO and only -z,relro to enable partial RELRO.

nx.description: The shared object does not have NX bit set. NX bit offer protection against exploitation of memory corruption vulnerabilities by marking memory page as non-executable. Use option --noexecstack or -z noexecstack to mark stack as non executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object does not have a stack canary value added to the stack. Stack canaries are used to detect and prevent exploits from overwriting return address. Use the option -fstack-protector-all to enable stack canaries.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object does not have RELRO enabled. The entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) are writable. "privacyPolicy" : "

Enjin Wallet

Privacy Policy
Last Updated: 28/07/12

This privacy policy (Privacy Policy) describes how Enjin Pte. Ltd. (Company Registration No. 201201984D) (Enjin) may collect, use, disclose and process your Personal Data. This Privacy Policy should be read together with the terms of service at enjinwallet.io/terms (Terms). Any capitalised expression used but not otherwise defined in this Privacy Policy shall have the meaning given to such expression in the Terms. For reference, Personal Data has the meaning given to it under the Personal Data Protection Act 2012 (No. 26 of 2012) (PDPA) or the applicable Data Protection Legislation.

1. General Information

1.1 Enjin is dedicated to managing, protecting and processing your Personal Data in accordance with its responsibilities under the PDPA.

1.2 By accessing the Platform, using the Services or submitting information to Enjin, you agree to Enjin collecting, using, disclosing, processing and sharing your Personal Data with its affiliates, service providers and relevant third parties in accordance with this Privacy Policy and the PDPA.

1.3 If you have any feedback, inquiries or complaints regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact Enjin at info@enjincoin.io and provide the relevant details.

2. Collection of Personal Data

2.1 When you access and use the Platform or the Services, you do so anonymously without having to provide any Personal Data. Notwithstanding, Enjin may collect Personal Data when (i) you contact Enjin, or request that Enjin contacts you, for any reason, or (ii) you submit your Personal Data to Enjin for any reason.

2.2 Enjin may use cookies, and other similar technologies to improve your user experience when you access the website. Whilst the use of the aforesaid technologies is not intended to collect any Personal Data, please note that Enjin has no control over the use of any of the aforesaid technology by third parties. You may at all times configure your browser to block, delete, restrict or otherwise control the aforesaid technologies but please note that this may impact your experience with the Platform and the Services.

2.3 Enjin may collect information relating to the general use of the Platform such as errors, log information concerning any errors encountered in the application and other related information relevant to Enjin's provision of the Services, for the purpose of administration and error analysis to help Enjin improve its Services.

2.4 If you provide Enjin with any Personal Data relating to a third party, by providing such Personal Data to Enjin, you represent and warrant to Enjin that you have obtained the consent of such third party and are authorised by the third party for the relevant purposes.

2.5 You shall ensure that all Personal Data submitted to Enjin is accurate and complete. Please note that failure to do so may result in, amongst others, Enjin being unable to respond to your request.

2.6 You may withdraw your consent at any time after giving reasonable notice by submitting your request to info@enjincoin.io. Following the withdrawal of your consent, Enjin shall no longer collect, use or disclose your Personal Data unless consent is again obtained or as authorised under the PDPA. The withdrawal of your consent may however result in certain consequences. In certain cases, Enjin may not be in the position to continue to provide its Services to you.

3. Purposes for Collection, Use and Disclosure of Personal Data

Any collection, use and disclosure of your Personal Data by Enjin shall be for the purpose of providing customer or technical support to you only.

4. Limitations

Enjin shall only collect, use or disclose your Personal Data to the extent necessary for the purposes described under this Privacy Policy and to the extent allowed under the PDPA.

5. Disclosure and Sharing of Your Personal Data

5.1 Enjin shall take reasonable steps to protect your Personal Data against unauthorised disclosure.

5.2 Enjin may disclose your Personal Data to third parties (e.g. affiliates, service provides or support agents) who are engaged to provide services to Enjin or who help Enjin in the course of its business operations. In the event Enjin so discloses Personal Data, such third parties will only have access to your Personal Data to the extent necessary to perform their functions and Enjin will conduct oversight over such service providers to ensure the secure management of Personal Data.

5.3 Enjin reserves the right to disclose your Personal Data in compliance with Applicable Laws.

5.4 Enjin does not sell your Personal Data to any third parties.

5.5 In the event that Enjin is in possession of any Personal Data, Enjin may transfer, store, process or deal with such Personal Data outside Singapore. In doing so, Enjin shall continue to comply with the PDPA and applicable Data Protection Legislation.

6. Protecting Your Information

6.1 Enjin shall take reasonable steps to secure and protect your Personal Data (if any) in its possession or control by making reasonable security arrangements to prevent unauthorised access, collection, use, disclosure, modification, disposal or similar risks to Personal Data.

6.2 Notwithstanding, Enjin cannot ensure the security of the information you transmit to Enjin via the Internet or the Platform, and shall not be liable for any Losses arising from any unauthorised collection, use or disclosure of Personal Data whatsoever.

7. Retention Enjin shall collect and retain personal data in accordance with this Privacy Policy for as long as it is necessary, required, or relevant for business or legal purposes.

8. Access and Correction You may request access or make correction to your Personal Data held with Enjin. Enjin reserves the right to charge a fee for processing your request for access, and such fee shall depend on the nature and complexity of your request.

9. Third Party Sites The Platform may contain links to other websites of third parties. This Privacy Policy only applies to this Platform and the third party websites are subject to their own privacy policies. Your access of these websites shall be at your own risk, and Enjin recommends that you review the privacy policies (and such other policies) relating to such third party websites.

10. Changes to the Privacy Policy

10.1 Enjin may amend this Privacy Policy from time to time for compliance with the Applicable Laws and for consistency with the manner Enjin deals with your Personal Data.

10.2 Any amended Privacy Policy shall be posted on this page, and effective with effect from such date of posting. By continuing to access the Platform or using the Services after such amended Privacy Policy has been posted, you are deemed to have agreed and consented to such revised Privacy Policy.

11. Governing Law

This Privacy Policy and any dispute or claim (including non-contractual disputes or claims) arising out of or in connection with it or its subject matter or formation shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of Singapore."

playstore_details.title: Enjin: Bitcoin, Ethereum, NFT Crypto Wallet
playstore_details.description:
Built for crypto trading

⚔️ Impenetrable
🛡️ Trustworthy
🔐 Privacy first
✅ Independent audit approved
📋 Paper-powered 12-word backup
⛓️ Hardware wallet tracking

Buy, sell, send, hodl or exchange Bitcoin, NFTs, tokens & other 100+ cryptocurrencies easily from your Enjin smart wallet. Unlock capabilities of decentralized exchanges to help manage your crypto portfolio & wealth in a single app.

Download Free Enjin Wallet Now!
Meet your new blockchain & cryptocurrency wallet

It's impenetrable, feature-packed, & convenient—supporting Bitcoin (BTC), Ethereum (ETH), Binance Coin (BNB), Litecoin (LTC), Dogecoin (DOGE), ERC-20, ERC-721, & ERC-1155 tokens & NFTs.

Built for crypto traders, holders, NFT traders, & gamers, the user-friendly Enjin blockchain & crypto wallet feature a marketplace for trading blockchain assets, DApp browser for interacting with DApps and DeFi platforms, blockchain gaming support, & in-app token swap featuring Kyber, Bancor, Changelly.

MANAGE INFINITE BLOCKCHAIN WALLETS

Create, import, use, and track an infinite number of crypto wallets—all in a streamlined, easy-to-use app. Create wallets for Bitcoin (BTC), Ethereum (ETH), Litecoin (LTC), Binance Coin (BNB), Dogecoin (DOGE), ERC-20, ERC-721, Coinbase, & Polkadot (DOT), & ERC-1155.

STORE & TRADE BLOCKCHAIN ASSETS

Stash your blockchain assets & collectables & trade them on the Enjin Marketplace. We've made buying assets as simple as the scan of a QR code & selling them as easy as a few taps of a screen.

CLAIM FREE TOKENS

Scan a QR code to instantly receive ERC-20 airdrops, altcoins, or valuable ERC-721 & ERC-1155 digital assets & NFTs.

RECLAIM YOUR PRIVACY

No annoying ads. Zero trackers. Your private keys are your own.

CONVERT CRYPTO WITH EASE

Swap hundreds of crypto tokens from thousands of available trading pairs instantly & directly via our exchange partners Kyber, Bancor, & Changelly. In-app token swap supports ERC-20 tokens, Bitcoin (BTC), Ethereum (ETH), Dogecoin (DOGE), & Litecoin (LTC).

ENJOY SEAMLESS BROWSING

Interact with any DApp or DeFi swap—without leaving the safety of your crypto wallet.

PROTECT YOUR ASSETS

We take security seriously, & so should you. Independently audited with pioneering security features unlike any other wallet, the Enjin Wallet turns your phone into a hardware-like blockchain & crypto wallet.

USE THE SAMSUNG BLOCKCHAIN KEYSTORE

We've partnered with Samsung to seamlessly integrate the Enjin Wallet with the Samsung Blockchain Keystore.

ENJOY YOUR NEW BLOCKCHAIN WALLET

Your new crypto wallet is built for convenience:
✅  Fingerprint Unlock: Use your fingerprint to immediately check your cryptocurrency portfolio without needing to enter yet another password.
✅  Hardware Wallet Tracking: Tired of cables? Use the Enjin Wallet to easily track your hardware wallet balance & transactions. Track Trezor, Ledger, & other hardware wallets.
✅  Auto-Add Tokens: Automatically add & detect tokens from the blockchain wallets you import or track.
✅  Custom Fees & Limits: Use optimized, dynamic fee, & gas calculation—or set your own custom fees and limits.
✅  Import & Sweep: Import from all major blockchain wallets such as Trust and Coin base in a few easy steps, & sweep Bitcoin and Litecoin.
✅  Local Currency: View balances in your local currency.
✅  Multilingual: Support for over 30 languages.

ABOUT ENJIN

Founded in 2009 & based in Singapore, Enjin offers an ecosystem of integrated blockchain products that make it easy to create, manage, explore, distribute, & integrate blockchain-based assets and NFTs.

The Enjin ecosystem is fueled by Enjin Coin (ENJ), a cryptocurrency used to directly back the value of next-generation blockchain assets.

SUPPORT & CONTACT

Have questions or need support? Visit our support center at https://enjin.io/help or contact us at support@enjin.io.
